Package: gfcanalysis
Version: 1.3
Date: 2015-11-20
Title: Tools for Working with Hansen et al. Global Forest Change Dataset
Authors@R: c(person("Alex", "Zvoleff", email="azvoleff@conservation.org",
    role=c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Alex Zvoleff <azvoleff@conservation.org>
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10.0),
    raster,
    methods
Imports:
    rgdal,
    geosphere,
    RCurl,
    rgeos,
    plyr,
    ggplot2,
    grid,
    sp,
    stringr,
    animation,
    rasterVis
Enhances: snow
Description: The gfcanalysis package supports analyses using the Global
    Forest Change dataset released by Hansen et al.. gfcanalysis was
    written for the Tropical Ecology Assessment and Monitoring (TEAM) Network
    (http://www.teamnetwork.org). For additional details on the Global Forest
    Change dataset, see: Hansen, M. et al. 2013.  "High-Resolution Global Maps
    of 21st-Century Forest Cover Change." Science 342 (15 November): 850-53.
    Data and more information is available on-line from:
    http://earthenginepartners.appspot.com
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: http://azvoleff.com/gfcanalysis
BugReports: https://github.com/azvoleff/gfcanalysis/issues
LazyData: true
